### 7. Hypothesis Testing — The Framework

```
Step 1: Define H₀ and H₁
Step 2: Choose test (T-test / Chi-Square / Z-test)
Step 3: Set α = 0.05 (standard)
Step 4: Run test → get p-value
Step 5: p < 0.05 → Reject H₀ (result is REAL!)
         p > 0.05 → Accept H₀ (could be chance)
```

---

### 8. Which Test to Use?

| Situation | Test |
|-----------|------|
| Compare 2 group means (numeric) | T-Test |
| Compare 2 categories | Chi-Square |
| Compare more than 2 groups | ANOVA |
| A/B test (conversions) | Z-Test / T-Test |

```python
# T-Test:
from scipy import stats
t_stat, p_value = stats.ttest_ind(group_a, group_b)

# Chi-Square:
chi2, p_value, dof, expected = stats.chi2_contingency(contingency_table)
```

