## ⚠️ Common Mistakes to Avoid

- ❌ Using mean for skewed data → ✅ Use median
- ❌ Saying "correlated = caused" → ✅ Correlation ≠ Causation!
- ❌ np.log() on data with 0s → ✅ Use np.log1p()
- ❌ Small sample size for A/B test → ✅ Minimum 1000 per group
- ❌ Running test then deciding α → ✅ Always set α=0.05 BEFORE test
- ❌ One test and done → ✅ Multiple tests for different angles

